To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the New York Freedom of Information Law, I hereby request the following records:

All contracts between Wanda L. DeOliveira, acting in her private capacity, and the Richmond County District Attorney's Office, signed between January 2020 and the present.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

Chris Gelardi

title: body cam footage for report AHP24-000856 five minutes before and fifteen minutes after the call was responded to by the officer.

communications.communication:
To Whom It May Concern:

Pursuant to the Illinois Freedom of Information Act., I hereby request the following records:

Please provide officer body cam footage for report AHP24-000856 fifteen minutes before and fifteen minutes after the call was responded to by the officers.

John Mc Keogh called the police to enforce 720 ILCS 5/10-5.5 Unlawful visitation or parenting time interference @ 103 W Canterbury Arlington heights Il 60004. Sunday 01/14/2024 at 12:00pm
Please provide full body cam and audio of the call made to Michelle Focht as it is part of evidence for violating the agreed and sign judge's order to produce the minor child Sloane Mc Keogh for visitation with the father John James Mc Keogh every Sundays 12 noon until five pm every Sunday. The police called Michelle Focht at 708-917-0629 to find out why she was not at 103 W Canterbury dr Arlington Heights Il 60004.

Michelle Focht and the minor child who is my daughter are not protected by any privacy laws as you formally replied the original FOIA Request 24-219 The conversations between the office, Michelle, and my daughter Sloane are part of evidence in the 720 ILCS 5/10-5.5 violation. This is also to serve as a formal letter to preserve evidence as part of Case No. 2023 D 79538

140/7 (1)(e): Security of lock up, detention area/ inside squad car.

140/7 (b)/(c): radio traffic, computer screen regarding other people-privacy and personal information 

Please provide officer body cam footage for report AHP24-000856 fifteen minutes before and fifteen minutes after the call was responded to by the officer all the information about the parties in the recorded footage is known and I am the father of the child.

The requested documents will be made available to the general public, and this request is not being made for commercial purposes.

In the event that there are fees, I would be grateful if you would inform me of the total charges in advance of fulfilling my request. I would prefer the request filled electronically, by e-mail attachment if available or CD-ROM if not.

Thank you in advance for your anticipated cooperation in this matter. I look forward to receiving your response to this request within 5 business days, as the statute requires.

Sincerely,

John James Mc Keogh

title: Files related to the Presidential Task Force on Regulatory Relief (1981 - 1988)

communications.communication:

Specifically, the folder marked "Interest Group Files including consumer, environment, farm, and labor (2.0 feet)" AND the folder marked "Gray, C. Boyden - Legal Counsel, 1981-1988 (18.0 feet)"
